channel.title: Earnings
channel.description: Corporate Company Earnings, Find Earnings Per Share and Earnings History Online

item.title: Wells Fargo's fourth-quarter revenue tops estimate, profit jumps
item.description: The fourth biggest U.S. bank by assets posted quarterly revenue that exceeded analysts' expectations.

item.title: Citigroup shares slide after fourth-quarter profit declines 26%
item.description: Citigroup shares were under pressure Friday after the banking giant reported a steep profit drop for the fourth quarter.

item.title: JPMorgan shares fall 6% after CFO lowers guidance on 'headwinds’ including wage inflation
item.description: The bank's CFO issued guidance Friday, saying he expected "headwinds" of higher expenses and moderating Wall Street revenue to cause returns to dip.

item.title: Delta keeps 2022 profit forecast on travel rebound despite omicron
item.description: Delta expects travel to recover this spring after cases of the omicron variant peak.

item.title: Apple chipmaker TSMC notches another quarterly sales record on strong demand
item.description: TSMC, which makes chips for companies like Apple, reported a sixth straight quarter of record sales as demand for its products rose amid a supply crunch.

item.title: Bed Bath & Beyond's supply chain issues hammered results. Its stock is up anyway
item.description: Bed Bath & Beyond CEO Mark Tritton said a lack of inventory due to supply chain bottlenecks cost the retailer about $100 million.

item.title: Walgreens shares give up gains after company warns of rising labor costs to keep up with Covid vaccines and tests
item.description: Walgreens said it administered 15.6 million Covid vaccines in the latest quarter — bringing its total to more than 56 million to date.

item.title: Nike shares rise as earnings, sales top estimates, fueled by strong North American demand
item.description: Nike CEO John Donahoe said the retailer is in a "much stronger competitive position" than it was pre-pandemic.

item.title: Darden shares fall as CEO announces plans to retire; Olive Garden parent raises forecast despite planned wage hike
item.description: Olive Garden parent Darden Restaurants announced that CEO Gene Lee will retire May 29.

item.title: Adobe plunges 10% and has second-worst day in past decade on weak guidance
item.description: Adobe's guidance for its fiscal first quarter badly missed analysts' estimates, sending the stock down more than 10%.

item.title: Lowe's says pandemic-fueled home improvement demand could cool in year ahead
item.description: During an analyst meeting, Lowe's Chief Financial Officer Dave Denton said the retailer is preparing for a "modest sector pullback in 2022."

item.title: Lululemon earnings top estimates, but shares fall after retailer cuts forecast for Mirror sales
item.description: Lululemon's stock gave up gains Thursday after the company slashed its sales expectations for Mirror, the at-home fitness device it acquired last year.

item.title: Oracle swings to loss because of payment tied to dispute over former CEO Hurd's employment
item.description: Oracle's results were clouded by a payment tied to the employment of Mark Hurd, previously co-CEO of the database software maker with current CEO Safra Catz.

item.title: GameStop shares fall as video game retailer reports widening losses in third quarter
item.description: GameStop shares fell after the video game retailer reported that its losses widened in the fiscal third quarter.

item.title: Rent the Runway posts widening losses, as subscribers have yet to return to pre-pandemic levels
item.description: Rent the Runway booked a wider fiscal third-quarter loss compared with 2020, as its sales shot up 66% year over year.

item.title: Stitch Fix shares crater as retailer cuts forecast, despite topping earnings estimates
item.description: Stitch Fix cut its revenue outlook for the fiscal year, saying that it faces ongoing supply chain pressures and is in a transition period for bringing on users.

item.title: MongoDB shares jump as revenue growth accelerates
item.description: While MongoDB continues to spend heavily in a competitive market, it's raising expectations for the quarter ahead.

item.title: DocuSign plunges almost 30% after e-signature company issues weak fourth-quarter guidance
item.description: DocuSign lost more than a quarter of its value after hours on Thursday following a disappointing forecast for the end of the year.

item.title: Kay Jewelers parent Signet shares down as investors fear retailer will have trouble sustaining strong growth
item.description: Amid ongoing global supply chain issues, Signet CEO Virginia Drosos said the retailer secured its holiday merchandise early this year.

item.title: Dollar General tested a store for wealthier shoppers. Now, it will grow to 1,000 locations
item.description: Dollar General plans to expand its Popshelf chain to about 1,000 locations. The new format helps the discounter attract suburban customers and drive up profits.

item.title: Snowflake stock soars on strong revenue and Q4 guidance
item.description: Shares of Snowflake were up more than 13% after it surpassed analyst expectations for third-quarter revenue and provided strong product revenue guidance.

item.title: Salesforce fourth quarter guidance misses Wall Street expectations
item.description: Salesforce said earnings per share for the December quarter would be between 72 and 73 cents, lower than Refinitiv analyst expectations of 81 cents.

item.title: Eco-friendly shoemaker Allbirds posts wider loss despite 33% gain in quarterly sales; shares fall
item.description: Allbirds' losses widened as the cost of opening stores and listing its stock weighed on its results.

item.title: Gap shares crater 15% after retailer sees millions in lost sales from delayed product shipments, cuts its forecast
item.description: Gap Inc. on Tuesday slashed its full-year outlook due to supply chain complications that put a damper on its third-quarter sales and took a bite out of profits.

item.title: Nordstrom shares tumble more than 20% as earnings fall short, hurt by higher labor costs, weak Nordstrom Rack sales
item.description: Nordstrom earnings fell short of analysts' expectations as labor costs ate into profits and sales struggled to return to pre-pandemic levels.

item.title: Dick's Sporting Goods shares fall despite earnings beat and hiked outlook
item.description: Dick's Sporting Goods on Tuesday reported fiscal third-quarter earnings and sales that outpaced analysts' expectations.

item.title: Best Buy earnings top estimates but retailer's stock tumbles amid weakening demand, shipping bottlenecks
item.description: Best Buy's fourth quarter could be hurt by rising shipping costs and weaker demand for consumer electronics.

item.title: Zoom beats estimates even as revenue growth is poised to slow after pandemic
item.description: Zoom indicated that revenue growth will slow to 19% in the current quarter, compared with over 300% growth last year following the onset of the coronavirus.

item.title: Kohl's shares jump after retailer reports 16% sales increase as shoppers buy clothes and makeup
item.description: The department store chain also raised its forecast for the year.

item.title: Macy's shares surge on upbeat earnings, decision to hire AlixPartners to review business
item.description: Macy's reported third-quarter earnings and sales that topped analysts' expectations, leading the department store chain to raise its full-year forecast.
